{
  "texts": [
    "The filters act as a sliding window across the image, allowing CNN to learn information from nearby cells.",
    "Weight sharing uses the same filter within the same layer throughout the image; when CNN is used to identify photos of cats vs. non-cats, the same filter is employed in the same layer to detect the cat's nose and ears.",
    "Throughout the image, the same weight (or kernel or filter in CNNs) is applied [33].",
    "GCNs were first introduced in \"Spectral Networks and Deep Locally Connected Networks on Graphs\" [34].GCNs, which learn features by analyzing neighboring nodes, carry out similar behaviors.",
    "The primary difference between CNNs and GNNs is that CNNs are made to operate on regular (Euclidean) ordered data."
  ]
}